        <lb L="25"> Compromise in his <rhyme verb="5">talk</rhyme>— </lb>
        <lb L="26"> For a man must crawl </lb>
        <lb L="27">Before he can <rhyme verb="5">walk</rhyme>— </lb>
        <lb L="28"> And in Alabama in '85</lb>
        <lb L="29"> A joker was lucky </lb>
        <lb L="30"> To be alive. </lb>
        <lb L="31"> But Booker T. </lb>
        <lb L="32"> Was nobody's <rhyme verb="6">fool:</rhyme>
        </lb>
        <lb L="33"> You may carve a dream </lb>
        <lb L="34"> With an humble <rhyme verb="6">tool.</rhyme>
        </lb>
        <lb L="35"> The tallest tower </lb>
        <lb L="36">Can tumble <rhyme verb="7">down</rhyme>
        </lb>
        <lb L="37"> If it be not rooted</lb>
        <lb L="38"> In solid <rhyme verb="7">ground.</rhyme>
        </lb>
